cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about using convolutional neural networks for biomedical image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a generative probabilistic model, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of anatomical priors is a unique aspect of this paper, which could also be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
